<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1905-11-09T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1905-11-09T00:00:00-05:00" n="501" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d501">
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                Minister <persName type="to">Powell</persName>.</hi></head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1905-11-09"><hi rend="italic">November 9,
                                1905</hi></date>.</dateline>
                            <seg rendition="#left">No. 722.]</seg></opener>
                        <p><hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I inclose herewith a copy of a letter<note n="a" xml:id="d501fna">Not printed.</note> from Mr. A. Lagojannis,
                            of Port au Prince, transmitting to the Department a copy of a letter
                            which is addressed to your legation on the 10th ultimo, in regard to the
                            Haitian Government’s refusal to permit foreigners to engage in retail
                            business in Haiti.</p>
                        <p>You are requested to report to the Department whether Mr. Lagojannis is
                            an American citizen.</p>
                        <p>I am, etc.,</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Elihu Root.</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>